name: NYDailyNews
text:
If there is any doubt that Dustin Johnson is the best player in the world, he can erase that in the fourth round of the Masters.

He needs to shoot 3-under to break the Masters scoring record shared by Spieth and Tiger Woods (1997), @XNYDNHankGola writes.
https://t.co/c9W7trfybf

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Saturday marked 60 years to the day since Ruby Bridges walked into an all-white elementary school in New Orleans as a mob of bigots hurled insults, eggs and tomatoes at an exceptionally brave Black girl.
https://t.co/knoJ4KfKva

name: NYDailyNews
text:
“I’m feeling pain ... They were hitting me pretty bad,” Ekim Kaya said, the day after he lost his $240,000 Lamborghini when car thieves beat him on the West Side of Manhattan.

One of the thieves got behind the wheel — but he didn’t know how to handle it.
https://t.co/KdmVz4Od1s

name: NYDailyNews
text:
JUST IN | The man accused of sucker-punching the “Honey, I Shrunk the Kids” star Rick Moranis was arrested, police said.

Marquis Ventura, 35, was collared by officers who recognized his face from wanted pictures and video released after the Oct. 1 attack.
https://t.co/KNWkU4Gma8
